data.title: Pretty average
data.text: Had heard this was a really great place to eat so went to give it a try. The service was good but the food wasn't worth the hype. Just average asian food. The portions were smaller than most of the local places.

data.title: Another Wow in Appleton
data.text:
Went here for a little girls' birthday party.  She just turned ten years old, and this is the place she chose to have her birthday dinner.  What does that say about quality of food?  That' it's the best damn Chinese you're going to find in a 50 mile radius, that's what!  
I of course always test Asian food by how well they serve the eggplant, and Dong Po made sure to set the bar high.  I will definitely need to spend some time in the kitchen learning how to reverse engineer the Eggplant Stuffed with Shrimp.  Absolutely delectable!

The only disappointment was the kiddie cocktail which was easily corrected.  They added orange juice to it.  We were not fans of that, but the server quickly replaced the foul drink with the correct replacement.

data.title: Fine Dining Chinese
data.text: They definitely put in the effort to make the atmosphere that of fine dining.  Even the plate of food have the accent of a hibiscus flower!  Starting out with wonton soup which was decent but only had one dumpling in it.  My husband ordered the orange beef and while the sauce was good, the fried beef was tough and stringy.  The others at our table ordered different chicken dishes that were much better!  I especially loved the orange chicken.  A nice Chinese restaurant though in the end!

data.title: Excellent Food!
data.text: I have gone here regularly for 15+ years. The food quality is great, the portions are good and the prices are very fair. They have the best General Tsao's Chicken and Shrimp I have ever had and their Cashew Chicken is also the best I've ever had. From all white meat to excellent breading, sauces and light crisp wraps for Egg Rolls and Crab Rangoon's the quality they give you for the price is excellent. Don't skip ordering the Crab Rangoons as they are the best I've ever had as well. This is a restaurant I will regular for a long, long time!

data.title: very slow for lunch, but good food
data.text: I like this as a go to for pick up chinese at night, but I've been disappointed when I've stopped for lunch. They just take a long time for lunch. I don;t know why but it has happened on multiple occasions. At night, the service is faster. The sushi is good, and they are consistent. Good value for the money.

data.title: Great food!
data.text: Average sevice, excellent food. Service has been excellent but really varies depending on server. Long time customer

data.title: Top Shelf!
data.text: Been going to Dong Po (and its predecessors at that location, all the way back to "Lum's") for many years. Always enjoyed its broad menu, excellent food and service, nice ambience, and incredibly modest prices, but never wrote a review of it. Just had a dinner experience with a couple visiting from FL who enjoy the most elegant and pricey restaurants wherever they travel. They raved so enthusiastically about Dong Po that I felt compelled to write this review. Three of us had different shrimp dishes (my wife is allergic), and each was superb. The shrimp were very nice sized, done to perfection, and generous in quantity, accompanied by crisp, fresh, nicely cooked veggies in tasty sauces. The presentation (with small orchids on each entree plate) was noteworthy. Can't end this review without special mention of their hot and sour soup: it is the best I've had anywhere, and we often order a quart "to go" after a lunch or dinner at Dong Po!

data.title: Terrible!
data.text: Terrible service. I have been ordering from there for months. As usual, they tell me 45 minutes to deliver but an hour and 10 minutes late there's still no sign of food. I called to inquire about my order and I was told they have a new driver it'll be there soon. Then after some mumbling on the other end of the line I cannot make out I was told they no longer deliver to my address when they are busy.  It's very disappointing that customers are only valued when it's convenient. I'll be getting my food from elsewhere from now on.

data.title: best sushi in town
data.text: I absolutely adore this place, the sushi just amazing.Very humble people and great service.... if you look for good sushi here the place.

data.title: Terrible Take Out
data.text:
I had take out from Dong Po last night, the Steak Bits off the House specialty menu.  Menu described the steak as tenderloin.  What I took home was not tenderloin, tender or even tasty.  It was overcooked, dry and tough.

Never again.

data.title: Great Sushi
data.text: My wife and I have been here several times.  She is a big fan of their sushi, in particular the Valentine roll.  I really enjoy their soup.  The restaurant doesn't look like much but the food is good.  The service is great and the prices are reasonable.  My in-laws frequently order take-out from here and always have good experiences.

data.title: Great food, good value!
data.text: I have been going to Dong Po for many years and between the crab rangoon and the general tsaos chicken and shrimp entrees they are hard to beat! I've never had better anywhere else and I love Chinese food!

data.title: We go often for the sushi
data.text: Seems to be the best sushi in the area. We have been here a couple dozen times and typically focus on their specialty rolls. Definitely on the sweet side, but highly recommend the lobster cha cha, followed by the Phoenix and "incredible" rolls.

data.title: Crowded, but means the food is good :)
data.text: I absolutely love their Orange Beef. I ask for it with broccoli and there are no problems getting it like that. Wait staff can be a bit slow, but you really only need them to refill drinks - and they don't mind being hailed over to you. Lots of laughs there, and delicious food.

data.title: My favorite
data.text: This is my favorite place to go for Sushi rolls. yum. yum! My husband loves the Cashew Chicken. good convenient location down town Appleton.

data.title: Very Disappointing
data.text:
During the second day of the elite 8 we ordered take out.  This was our first time based on several reviews.  We ordered sweet and sour shrimp, sesame shrimp and three spring rolls.  

Upon opening the bag we found three greasy EGG rolls, and two dinners that had the thickest batter we have ever seen on shrimp.  I have ordered S&S shrimp from many places and never was given it battered.  Does not make sense because when you pour the sauce (more like a sickening sweet syrup) it becomes a soggy mess.  I peeled off the breaking and with a few pieces of green pepper and canned pineapple I barely made a meal...a very overpriced one.

My wife attempted to eat her sesame shrimp but complained that it was too salty and too heavy.  We wished that we had gone back to the place on Ballard Ave where we had lunch the day prior.

That was our first and last visit.  BTW, if you have a partner to go in and get the order then park toward the back where you can see the employee entrance.  You might see some odd things going on at the doorway.

data.title: Greasy.
data.text: Food was ok. I had orange chicken, egg rolls, and chicken wings. Extremely greasy. I went here because of the good reviews.  I will probably not go back.

data.title: Carry Out Staple
data.text: It's very rare that we eat here, but quite common for us to carry out Sushi and occasional entrees. Staff is always helpful and happy. I usually enjoy a Tsing Tau at the bar while waiting for my order to be prepared and chat at the Sushi chef. This place is quite often devoid of dine-in clientele, and I don't know if that has to do with food quality or something else? Dining area is clean, well-lit and comfortable. We order out such anywhere from once a month to once a week. Their crab rangoon are a favorite and their sushi, while not quite up there with Nakashima's, is VERY good and a little easier on the wallet. I would recommend to anyone for carry-out but have limited experience dining in.

data.title: Great!
data.text:
I've ordered delivery from here several times. Can't recommend them enough! Delivery is always on point. Tonight they told me 45 minutes but they were here in 30 minutes. A great Monday night solution. 

Love that they deliver sushi, decent sushi - it's not common in small town Midwest.

data.title: outstanding in every way
data.text: My wife and I had the lobster cha cha roll. Outstanding. Service was excellent. Certainly worth the trip!
